I encountered the same problem with the HTTP ping.  Changing
the case of the argument to the getaddrinfo call fixed the
problem for me \(patch below\). I haven't tried the other ping
types.

diff -u -r echoping-5.0.1.orig/echoping.h
echoping-5.0.1/echoping.h
\--- echoping-5.0.1.orig/echoping.h      2002-10-11
05:12:53.000000000 -0700
+++ echoping-5.0.1/echoping.h   2003-06-25
00:35:05.000000000 -0700
@@ -114,7 +114,7 @@
\#define        ECHO\_TCP\_PORT   &amp;quot;echo&amp;quot;
\#define        DISCARD\_TCP\_PORT        &amp;quot;discard&amp;quot;
\#define        CHARACTER\_GENERATOR\_TCP\_PORT    &amp;quot;chargen&amp;quot;
-\#define DEFAULT\_HTTP\_TCP\_PORT &amp;quot;HTTP&amp;quot;
+\#define DEFAULT\_HTTP\_TCP\_PORT &amp;quot;http&amp;quot;
\#define DEFAULT\_HTTPS\_TCP\_PORT &amp;quot;HTTPS&amp;quot;
\#define DEFAULT\_ICP\_UDP\_PORT &amp;quot;ICP&amp;quot;

